    "recap_url": "https://www.12thman.com/news/2026/3/13/no-22-baseball-falls-to-no-9-oklahoma-8-7-after-late-rally-in-sec-opener",
    "recap_headline": "Texas A&M",
    "recap_text": "NORMAN\u00a0\u2013\nNo. 22 Texas A&M fell to No. 9 Oklahoma, 8-7, in a Friday night thriller from Kimrey Family Stadium.\nThe Aggies (15-2) spotted four runs in the first inning to get ahead early. Oklahoma (16-2) answered with two runs on a double and a pair of triples in the bottom half of the first to cut the lead to two.\nIn the top of the third,\nBear Harrison\ndrove an RBI double to put the Aggies up 5-2, but the Sooners responded with two more runs in the bottom half to make it a 5-4 game.\nWesley Jordan\nscratched two runs back for the Maroon & White in the top of the sixth to go up 7-4. Oklahoma answered right back in the bottom of the sixth with a pair of home runs to even the score at seven.\nThe Sooners delivered the final blow in the bottom of the eighth with a bases loaded sacrifice fly to go ahead, 8-7.\nChris Hacopian\nled the Aggie offense, going 2-for-3 with a double and two walks. The junior second baseman scored a run and drove in one RBI.\nShane Sdao\nworked 3.2 innings as the starter, suffering four earned runs on eight hits and a walk.\nEthan Darden\n,\nJuan Vargas\n,\nJosh Stewart\n,\nHunter Vincent\nand\nClayton Freshcorn\neach made appearances in relief. Darden and Vincent each dealt scoreless outings in 1.0 and 1.1 innings pitched, respectively. Freshcorn (2-1) suffered his first loss of the season after allowing the go-ahead sacrifice fly in the eighth inning.\nTOP PLAYERS\nChris Hacopian\n\u2013 2-for-3, 1 R, 1 RBI, 1 2B, 2 BB\nWesley Jordan\n\u2013 1-for-4, 1 R, 2 RBI, 2 BB\nHunter Vincent\n\u2013 1.1 IP, 0 H, 0 R, 0 BB, 2 K\nSCORING SUMMARY\nT1 |\nGavin Grahovac\nand\nCaden Sorrell\nboth walked to start the contest. Hacopian put the Aggies on the board with a double off the wall in left field to plate Grahovac. Jordan followed with a walk, and two more runs scored on a throwing error by the Sooners' third baseman off the bat of\nJake Duer\n.\nNico Partida\ngrounded out back to the pitcher's mound, advancing Duer to second and Jordan to third. Jordan scored the Maroon & White's fourth run of the frame on a passed ball. A&M 4, Oklahoma 0.\nB1 | Trey Gambill led off with a sharp double down the left field line and scored on a Brendan Brock triple off the wall in left-center field. Jaxon Willits plated the Sooners' second run on a sacrifice fly to center field. A&M 4, Oklahoma 2.\nT3 |\nTerrence Kiel II\nwalked with one out and was plated on a double from Harrison to left-center field. A&M 5, Oklahoma 2.\nB3 | Camden Johnson doubled to center field, followed by a walk from Brock. Willits singled through the right side to plate Johnson and Brock scored on a single from Deiten LaChance. A&M 5, Oklahoma 4.\nT6 |\nBoston Kellner\nwalked and Grahovac singled to left field. With two outs, Jordan drove a line drive to right-center field to plate both runs. A&M 7, Oklahoma 4.\nB6 | Jason Walk reached first on a walk. Brock homered to put the Sooners back within a run. On the next at-bat, Willits shot a home run to right field that evened the score. A&M 7, Oklahoma 7.\nT8 | Walk led off with a single to left field and Gambill was hit by a pitch. Johnson advanced both runners with a sacrifice bunt. Brock was intentionally walked, and Dasan Harris plated the go-ahead run with a sacrifice fly to center field. A&M 7, Oklahoma 8.\nGAME NOTES\nFriday's opener marked the 69th meeting all-time between the clubs. After the loss, the Aggies trail the series 35-34\n3,727 filled Kimrey Family Stadium for the SEC opener Friday night.\nHacopian's double in the opening frame was his first in the Maroon & White.\nGrahovac extended his hit streak to eight games and his on-base streak to 11 games.\nKellner and Kiel have reached base safely in all 17 games this season.\nSorrell has reached base safely in each of the last 11 games.\nUP NEXT\nTexas A&M continues the series with Oklahoma Saturday, March 14. First pitch is slated for 4 p.m. from Kimrey Family Park.\nFollow the Aggies\nVisit for more information on Texas A&M baseball. Fans can keep up to date with the A&M baseball team on\u00a0Facebook, Instagram\u00a0and X by following @aggiebaseball."
